obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (6512)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title, application and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00014_199442_1517807323753&sectionId=6512&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00014_199442_1517807323753
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `This Act may be called the Transplantation of`
  line `^1[Human Organs and Tissues] Act, 1994.`
  line
  line `(2) It applies, in the first instance, to the whole of the States of Goa, Himachal Pradesh and`
  line `Maharashtra and to all the Union territories and it shall also apply to such other State which adopts this`
  line `Act by resolution passed in that behalf under clause (1) of article 252 of the Constitution.`
  line
  line `(3) It shall come into force in the States of Goa, Himachal Pradesh and Maharashtra and in all the`
  line `Union territories on such date^2`
  line `as the Central Government may, by notification, appoint and in any`
  line `other State which adopts this Act under clause (1) of article 252 of the Constitution, on the date of such`
  line `adoption; and any reference in this Act to the commencement of this Act shall, in relation to any State`
  line `or Union territory, means the date on which this Act comes into force in such State or Union territory`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1 Subs. by s. 3, ibid., for "Human Organs" (w.e.f. 10-1-2014).`
  line
  line `2 4th February, 1995, vide Notification No. S.O. 80(E), dated the 4th February, 1995, see Gazette of India, Extraordinary, Part II,`
  line `sec. 3(ii).`
  line
  line `Extended to the Union territory of Jammu and Kashmir and Union territory of Ladakh by Act 34 of 2019, s. 95 and the Fifth`
  line `Schedule (w.e.f. 31-10-2019).`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (6513)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00014_199442_1517807323753&sectionId=6513&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00014_199442_1517807323753
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,--`
  line
  line `(a) "advertisement" includes any form of advertising whether to the public generally or to`
  line `any section of the public or, individually to selected persons;`
  line
  line `(b) "Appropriate Authority" means the Appropriate Authority appointed under section 13;`
  line
  line `(c) "Authorisation Committee" means the committee constituted under clause (a) or clause (b) of`
  line `sub-section (4) of section 9;`
  line
  line `(d) "brain-stem death" means the stage at which all functions of the brain-stem have`
  line `permanently and irreversibly ceased and is so certified under sub-section (6) of section 3;`
  line
  line `(e) "deceased person" means a person in whom permanent disappearance of all evidence of life`
  line `occurs, by reason of brain-stem death or in a cardio-pulmonary sense, at any time after live birth`
  line `has taken place;`
  line
  line `(f) "donor" means any person, not less than eighteen years of age, who voluntarily authorises the`
  line `removal of any of his human organs for therapeutic purposes under sub-section (1) or`
  line `sub-section (2) of section 3;`
  line
  line `(g) "hospital" includes a nursing home, clinic, medical centre, medical or teaching institution`
  line `for therapeutic purposes and other like institution;`
  line
  line `(h) "human organ" means any part of a human body consisting of a structured arrangement of`
  line `tissues which, if wholly, removed, cannot be replicated by the body;`
  line
  line `^1[(ha) "Human Organ Retrieval Centre" means a hospital,--`
  line
  line `(i) which has adequate facilities for treating seriously ill patients who can be potential`
  line `donours of organs in the event of death; and`
  line
  line `(ii) which is registered under sub-section (1) of section 14 for retrieval of human organs;]`
  line
  line `(hb) "minor" means a person who has not completed the age of eighteen years;`
  line
  line `^2[(i) "near relative" means spouse, son, daughter, father, mother, brother, sister, grandfather,`
  line `grandmother, grandson or granddaughter;]`
  line
  line `(j) "notification" means a notification published in the Official Gazette;`
  line
  line `(k) "payment" means payment in money or money's worth but does not include any payment`
  line `for defraying or reimbursing`
  line
  line `(i) the cost of removing, transporting or preserving the ^3[human organ or tissue or both] to be`
  line `supplied; or`
  line
  line `(ii) any expenses or loss of earnings incurred by a person so far as reasonably and directly`
  line `attributable to his supplying any human organ from his body;`
  line
  line `(l) "prescribed" means prescribed by rules made under this Act;`
  line
  line `(m) "recipient" means a person into whom any ^3[human organ or tissue or both] is, or is`
  line `proposed to be, transplanted;`
  line
  line `(n) "registered medical practitioner" means a medical practitioner who possesses any`
  line `recognised medical qualification as defined in clause (h) of section 2 of the Indian Medical`
  line `Council Act, 1956 (102 of 1956), and who is enrolled on a State Medical Register as defined in`
  line `clause (k) of that section;`
  line
  line `(o) "therapeutic purposes" means systematic treatment of any disease or the measures to`
  line `improve health according to any particular method or modality; ^3***`
  line
  line `^4[(oa) "tissue" means a group of cells, except blood, performing a particular function in the`
  line `human body;`
  line
  line `(ob) "tissue Bank" means a facility registered under section 14A for carrying out any activity`
  line `relating to the recovery, screening, testing, processing, storage and distribution of tissues, but does not`
  line `to include a Blood Bank;]`
  line
  line `(p) "transplantation" means the grafting of any human organ from any living person or`
  line `deceased person to some other living person for therapeutic purposes;`
  line
  line `^4[(q) "transplant co-ordinator" means a person appointed by the hospital for co-ordinating all`
  line `matters relating to removal or transplantation of human organs or tissues or both and for assisting the`
  line `authority for removal of human organs in accordance with the provisions of sections 3.]`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line `1 Ins. by Act 16 of 2011, s. 5 (w.e.f. 10-1-2014).`
  line
  line `2 Subs. by s. 5, ibid., for clause (i) (w.e.f. 10-1-2014).`
  line
  line `3 Subs. by s. 4, ibid., for "human organ" (w.e.f. 10-1-2014).`
  line
  line `4 Ins. by s. 5, ibid. (w.e.f. 10-1-2014).`
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (6514)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Authority for removal of human organs or tissues or both.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00014_199442_1517807323753&sectionId=6514&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00014_199442_1517807323753
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `^1[3. Authority for removal of ^1[human organs or tissues or both].-- (1) Any donor may, in such`
  line `manner and subject to such conditions as may be prescribed, authorise the removal, before his death,`
  line `of any ^2[human organ or tissue or both] of his body for therapeutic purposes.`
  line
  line `^3[(1A) For the purpose of removal, storage or transplantation of such human organs or tissues or both,`
  line `as may be prescribed, it shall be the duty of the registered medical practitioner working in a hospital, in`
  line `consultation with transplant co-ordinator, if such transplant co-ordinator is available,--`
  line
  line `(i) to ascertain from the person admitted to the Intensive Care Unit or from his near relative that`
  line `such person had authorised at any time before his death the removal of any human organ or tissue or`
  line `both of his body under sub-section (2), then the hospital shall proceed to obtain the documentation for`
  line `such authorisation;`
  line
  line `(ii) where no such authority as referred to in sub-section (2) was made by such person, to make`
  line `aware to that person or near relative for option to authorise or decline for donation of`
  line `human organs or tissues or both;`
  line
  line `(iii) to require the hospital to inform in writing to the Human Organ Removal Centre for removal,`
  line `storage or transplantation of human organs or tissues or both of the donor identified in`
  line `clauses (i) and (ii) in such manner as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(1B) The duties mentioned under clauses (i) to (iii) of sub-section (1A) from such date, as may be`
  line `prescribed, shall also apply in the case of a registered medical practitioner working in an Intensive Care`
  line `Unit in a hospital which is not registered under this Act for the purpose of removal, storage or`
  line `transplantation of human organs or tissues or both.]`
  line
  line `(2) If any donor had, in writing and in the presence of two or more witnesses`
  line `(at least one of whom is a near relative of such person), unequivocally authorised at any time before`
  line `his death, the removal of any human organ of his body, after his death, for therapeutic purposes,`
  line `the person lawfully in possession of the dead body of the donor shall, unless he has any reason to believe`
  line `that the donor had subsequently revoked the authority aforesaid, grant to a registered medical`
  line `practitioner all reasonable facilities for the removal, for therapeutic purposes, of that ^2[human organ or`
  line `tissue or both] from the dead body of the donor.`
  line
  line `(3) Where no such authority as is referred to in sub-section (2), was made by any person before his`
  line `death but no objection was also expressed by such person to any of his ^1[human organs or tissues or both]`
  line `being used after his death for therapeutic purposes, the person lawfully in possession of the dead body`
  line `of such person may, unless he has reason to believe that any near relative of the deceased person has`
  line `objection to any of the deceased persons ^1[human organs or tissues or both] being used for`
  line `therapeutic purposes, authorise the removal of any ^2[human organ or tissue or both] of the deceased`
  line `person for its use for therapeutic purposes.`
  line
  line `(4) The authority given under sub-section (1) or sub-section (2) or, as the case may be,`
  line `sub-section (3) shall be sufficient warrant for the removal, for therapeutic purposes, of the ^2[human`
  line `organ or tissue or both]; but no such removal shall be made by any person other than the registered`
  line `medical practitioner:`
  line
  line `^3[Provided that a technician possessing such qualifications and experience, as may be prescribed,`
  line `may enucleate a cornea.]`
  line
  line `(5) Where any ^2[human organ or tissue or both] is to be removed from the body of a deceased`
  line `person, the registered medical practitioner shall satisfy himself, before such removal, by a personal`
  line `examination of the body from which any ^2[human organ or tissue or both] is to be removed, that life is`
  line `extinct in such body or, where it appears to be a case of brain-stem death, that such death has been`
  line `certified under sub-section (6).`
  line
  line `(6) Where any ^2[human organ or tissue or both] is to be removed from the body of a person in the`
  line `event of his brain-stem death, no such removal shall be undertaken unless such death is certified, in such form and in such manner and on satisfaction of such conditions and requirements as may be prescribed,`
  line `by a Board of medical experts consisting of the following, namely:--`
  line
  line `(i) the registered medical practitioner in charge of the hospital in which brain-stem death has`
  line occurred;
  line
  line `(ii) an independent registered medical practitioner, being a specialist, to be nominated by the`
  line `registered medical practitioner specified in clause (i), from the panel of names approved by the`
  line `Appropriate Authority;`
  line
  line `(iii) a neurologist or a neurosurgeon to be nominated by the registered medical practitioner`
  line `specified in clause (i), from the panel of names approved by the Appropriate Authority:^4***`
  line
  line `^5[Provided that where a neurologist or a neurosurgeon is not available, the registered medical`
  line `practitioner may nominate an independent registered medical practitioner, being a surgeon or a`
  line `physician and an anaesthetist or intensivist subject to the condition that they are not members of the`
  line `transplantation team for the concerned recipient and to such conditions as may be prescribed;]`
  line
  line `(iv) the registered medical practitioner treating the person whose brain-stem death has occurred.`
  line
  line `(7) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (3), where brain-stem death of any person,`
  line `less than eighteen years of age, occurs and is certified under sub-section (6), any of the parents of the`
  line `deceased person may give authority, in such form and in such manner as may be prescribed, for the`
  line `removal of any ^6[human organ or tissue or both] from the body of the deceased person.]`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act of 16 of 2011, s. 4, for "human organs" (w.e.f. 10-1-2014).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 4, ibid., for "human organ" (w.e.f. 10-1-2014).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by s. 6, ibid. (w.e.f. 10-1-2014).`
  line
  line `4. The word "and" omitted by Act 16 of 2011, s. 6 (w.e.f. 10-1-2014).`
  line
  line `5. Ins. by s. 6, ibid. (w.e.f. 10-1-2014).`
  line
  line `6. Subs. by s. 4, ibid., for "human organ" (w.e.f. 10-1-2014).`
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (6515)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Removal of human organs or tissues or both not to be authorised in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00014_199442_1517807323753&sectionId=6515&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00014_199442_1517807323753
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `4. Removal of ^2[human organs or tissues or both] not to be authorised in certain cases.--(1) No`
  line `facilities shall be granted under sub-section (2) of section 3 and no authority shall be given under`
  line `sub-section (3) of that section for the removal of any ^1[human organ or tissue or both] from the body of a`
  line `deceased person, if the person required to grant such facilities, or empowered to give such authority, has`
  line `reason to believe that an inquest may be required to be held in relation to such body in pursuance of the`
  line `provisions of any law for the time being in force.`
  line
  line `(2) No authority for the removal of any ^1[human organ or tissue or both] from the body of a deceased`
  line `person shall be given by a person to whom such body has been entrusted solely for the purpose of`
  line `interment, cremation or other disposal.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by s. 4, ibid., for "human organ" (w.e.f. 10-1-2014).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 4, ibid., for "human organs" (w.e.f. 10-1-2014).`
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (6516)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Authority for removal of human organs or tissues or both in case of unclaimed bodies in hospital or prison.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00014_199442_1517807323753&sectionId=6516&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00014_199442_1517807323753
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `5. Authority for removal of ^2[human organs or tissues or both] in case of unclaimed bodies in`
  line `hospital or prison.--(1) In the case of a dead body lying in a hospital or prison and not claimed by any`
  line `of the near relatives of the deceased person within forty-eight hours from the time of the death of the`
  line `concerned person, the authority for the removal of any ^1[human organ or tissue or both] from the dead`
  line `body which so remains unclaimed may be given, in the prescribed form, by the person in charge, for`
  line `the time being, of the management or control of the hospital or prison, or by an employee of such`
  line `hospital or prison authorised in this behalf by the person in charge of the management or control thereof.`
  line
  line `(2) No authority shall be given under sub-section (1) if the person empowered to give such authority`
  line `has reason to believe that any near relative of the deceased person is likely to claim the dead body even`
  line `though such near relative has not come forward to claim the body of the deceased person within the time`
  line `specified in sub-section (1).`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by s. 4, ibid., for "human organ" (w.e.f. 10-1-2014).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 4, ibid., for "human organs" (w.e.f. 10-1-2014).`
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (6517)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Authority for removal of human organs or tissues or both from bodies sent for post-mortem examination for medico-legal or pathological purposes.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00014_199442_1517807323753&sectionId=6517&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00014_199442_1517807323753
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `6. Authority for removal of ^1[human organs or tissues or both] from bodies sent for`
  line `post-mortem examination for medico-legal or pathological purposes.-- Where the body of a person`
  line `has been sent for post-mortem examination--`
  line
  line `(a) for medico-legal purposes by reason of the death of such person having been caused by accident`
  line `or any other unnatural cause; or`
  line
  line `(b) for pathological purposes,`
  line
  line `the person competent under this Act to give authority for the removal of any ^2[human organ or tissue or`
  line `both] from such dead body may, if he has reason to believe that such ^2[human organ or tissue or both]`
  line `will not be required for the purpose for which such body has been sent for post-mortem examination,`
  line `authorise the removal, for therapeutic purposes, of that ^2[human organ or tissue or both] of the`
  line `deceased person provided that he is satisfied that the deceased person had not expressed, before his`
  line `death, any objection to any of his ^3[human organs or tissues or both] being used, for therapeutic purposes`
  line `after his death or, where he had granted an authority for the use of any of his ^3[human organs or`
  line `tissues or both] for therapeutic purposes, after his death, such authority had not been revoked by him`
  line `before his death.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by s. 4, ibid., for "human organs" (w.e.f. 10-1-2014).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 16 of 2011, s. 4 for "human organ" (w.e.f. 10-1-2014).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by s. 4, ibid., for "human organs" (w.e.f. 10-1-2014).`
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (6518)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Preservation of human organs or tissue or both.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00014_199442_1517807323753&sectionId=6518&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00014_199442_1517807323753
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `7. Preservation of ^2`
  line `[human organs or tissues or both].-- After the removal of any ^1[human organ`
  line `or tissue or both] from the body of any person, the registered medical practitioner shall take such`
  line `steps for the preservation of the ^1[human organ or tissue or both] so removed as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 16 of 2011, s. 4 for "human organ" (w.e.f. 10-1-2014).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 4, ibid., for "human organs" (w.e.f. 10-1-2014).`
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (6519)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title Savings.
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 16 of 2011, s. 4 for "human organ" (w.e.f. 10-1-2014).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00014_199442_1517807323753&sectionId=6519&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00014_199442_1517807323753
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `(1) Nothing in the foregoing provisions of this Act shall be construed as rendering`
  line `unlawful any dealing with the body or with any part of the body of a deceased person if such dealing`
  line `would have been lawful if this Act had not been passed.`
  line
  line `(2) Neither the grant of any facility or authority for the removal of any ^1[human organ or tissue`
  line `or both] from the body of a deceased person in accordance with the provisions of this Act nor the`
  line `removal oil any ^1[human organ or tissue or both] from the body of a deceased person in pursuance of`
  line `such authority shall be deemed to be an offence punishable under section 297 of the Indian Penal Code`
  line `(45 of 1860).`
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (6520)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Restrictions on removal and transplantation of human organs or tissues or both.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00014_199442_1517807323753&sectionId=6520&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00014_199442_1517807323753
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `9. Restrictions on removal and transplantation of ^2[human organs or tissues or both].--(1) Save`
  line `as otherwise provided in sub-section (3), no ^1[human organ or tissue or both] removed from the body of a`
  line `donor before his death shall be transplanted into a recipient unless the donor is a near relative of the`
  line recipient.
  line
  line `^3[(1A) Where the donor or the recipient being near relative is a foreign national, prior approval of the`
  line `Authorisation Committee shall be required before removing or transplanting human organ or tissue or`
  line `both:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Authorisation Committee shall not approve such removal or transplantation if the`
  line `recipient is a foreign national and the donor is an Indian national unless they are near relatives.`
  line
  line `(1B) No human organs or tissues or both shall be removed from the body of a minor before his death`
  line `for the purpose of transplantation except in the manner as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(1C) No human organs or tissues or both shall be removed from the body of a mentally challenge`
  line `person before his death for the purpose of transplantation.--`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purpose of this sub-section,--`
  line
  line `(i) the expression "mentally challenged person" includes a person with mental illness or mental`
  line `retardation, as the case may be;`
  line
  line `(ii) the expression "mental illness" includes dementia, schizophrenia and such other mental`
  line `condition that makes a person intellectually disables;`
  line
  line `(iii) the expression "mental retardation" shall have the same meaning as assigned to it in`
  line `clause (r) of section 2 of the Persons With Disabilities (Equal Opportunities, Protection of Right and`
  line `Full Participation) Act, 1995 (1 of 1996).]`
  line
  line `(2) Where any donor authorises the removal of any of his ^2[human organs or tissues or both] after`
  line `his death under sub-section (2) of section 3 or any person competent or empowered to give authority for`
  line `the removal of any ^1[human organ or tissue or both] from the body of any deceased person authorises`
  line `such removal, the ^1[human organ or tissue or both] may be removed and transplanted into the body of`
  line `any recipient who may be in need of such ^1[human organ or tissue or both].`
  line
  line `(3) If any donor authorises the removal of any of his ^2[human organs or tissues or both] before his`
  line `death under sub-section (1) of section 3 for transplantation into the body of such recipient, not being`
  line `a near relative, as is specified by the donor by reason of affection or attachment towards the recipient or for any other special reasons, such ^4[human organ or tissue or both] shall not be removed`
  line `and transplanted without the prior approval of the Authorisation Committee.`
  line
  line `^5[(3A) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (3), where--`
  line
  line `(a) any donor has agreed to make a donation of his human organ or tissue or both before his death`
  line `to a recipient, who is his near relative, but such donor is not compatible biologically as a donor for the`
  line `recipient; and`
  line
  line `(b) the second donor has agreed to make a donation of his human organ or tissue or both before`
  line `his death to such recipient, who is his near relative, but such donor is not compatible biologically as a`
  line `donor for such recipient; then`
  line
  line `(c) the first donor who is compatible biologically as a donor for the second recipient and the`
  line `second donor is compatible biologically as a donor of a human organ or tissue or both for the first`
  line `recipient and both donors and both recipients in the aforesaid group of donor and recipient have`
  line `entered into a single agreement to donate and receive such human organ or tissue or both according to`
  line `such biological compatibility in the group,`
  line
  line `the removal and transplantation of the human organ or tissue or both, as per the agreement referred to`
  line `above, shall not be done without prior approval of the Authorisation Committee.]`
  line
  line `^6[(4) (a) The composition of the Authorisation Committee shall be such as may be prescribed by the`
  line `Central Government from time to time.`
  line
  line `(b) The State Government and the Union territories shall constitute, by notification, one or more`
  line `Authorisation Committee consisting of such members as may be nominated by the State Government and`
  line `the Union territories on such terms and conditions as may be specified in the notification for the purposes`
  line `of this section.]`
  line
  line `(5) On an application jointly made, in such form and in such manner as may be prescribed, by`
  line `the donor and the recipient, the Authorisation Committee shall, after holding an inquiry and after`
  line `satisfying itself that the applicants have complied with all the requirements of this Act and tile rules`
  line `made thereunder, grant to the applicants approval for the removal and transplantation of the human`
  line organ.
  line
  line `(6) If, after the inquiry and after giving an opportunity to the applicants of being heard, the`
  line `Authorisation Committee is satisfied that the applicants have not complied with the requirements of`
  line `this Act and the rules made thereunder, it shall, for reasons to be recorded in writing, reject the`
  line `application for approval.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 16 of 2011, s. 4 for "human organ" (w.e.f. 10-1-2014).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 4, ibid., for "human organs" (w.e.f. 10-1-2014).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by s. 7, ibid. (w.e.f. 10-1-2014).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 16 of 2011, s. 4, for "human organ" (w.e.f. 10-1-2014).`
  line
  line `5. Ins. by s. 7, ibid. (w.e.f. 10-1-2014).`
  line
  line `6. Subs. by s. 7, ibid., for sub-section (4) (w.e.f. 10-1-2014).`
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (6521)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Regulation of hospital conducting the removal, storage or transplantation of human organs or tissue or both.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00014_199442_1517807323753&sectionId=6521&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00014_199442_1517807323753
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `10. Regulation of hospitals conducting the removal, storage or transplantation of`
  line `^2[human organs or tissues or both].-- (1) On and from the commencement of this Act,--`
  line
  line `(a) no hospital, unless registered under this Act, shall conduct, or associate with, or help in, the`
  line `removal, storage or transplantation of any ^1[human organ or tissue or both];`
  line
  line `(b) no medical practitioner or any other person shall conduct, or cause to be conducted, or`
  line `aid in conducting by himself or through any other person, any activity relating to the removal,`
  line `storage or transplantation of any ^1[human organ or tissue or both] at a place other than a place`
  line `registered under this Act; ^3***`
  line
  line `(c) no place including a hospital registered under sub-section (1) of section 15 shall be used`
  line `or cause to be used by any person for the removal, storage or transplantation of any`
  line `^1[human organ or tissue or both] except for therapeutic purposes;`
  line
  line ^4[and]
  line
  line `^5[(d) no Tissues Bank, unless registered under this Act, shall carry out any activity relating to the`
  line `recovery, screening, testing, processing, storage and distribution of tissues.]`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), the eyes or the ears may be removed at`
  line `any place from the dead body of any donor, for therapeutic purposes, by a registered medical practitioner.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this sub-section, "ears" includes ear drums and ear bones.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 16 of 2011, s. 4, for "human organ" (w.e.f. 10-1-2014).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 4, ibid., for "human organs" (w.e.f. 10-1-2014).`
  line
  line `3. The word "and" omitted by s. 8, ibid. (w.e.f. 10-1-2014).`
  line
  line `4. The word "and" ins by s. 8, ibid. (w.e.f. 10-1-2014).`
  line
  line `5. Ins. by s. 8, ibid. (w.e.f. 10-1-2014).`
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (6522)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Prohibition of removal or transplantation of human organs or tissues or both for any purpose other than therapeutic purpose.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00014_199442_1517807323753&sectionId=6522&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00014_199442_1517807323753
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `11. Prohibition of removal or transplantation of ^2`
  line `[human organs or tissues or both] for any`
  line `purpose other than the rapeatic purposes.-- No donor and no person empowered to give authority for`
  line `the removal of any human organ shall authorise the removal of any ^1[human organ or tissue or both] for`
  line `any purpose other than therapeutic purposes.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 16 of 2011, s. 4, for "human organ" (w.e.f. 10-1-2014).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 4, ibid., for "human organs" (w.e.f. 10-1-2014).`
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (6523)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Explaining effects, etc., to donor and recipient.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 16 of 2011, s. 4, for "human organ" (w.e.f. 10-1-2014).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00014_199442_1517807323753&sectionId=6523&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00014_199442_1517807323753
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `No registered medical practitioner`
  line `shall undertake the removal or transplantation of any ^1[human organ or tissue or both] unless he has`
  line `explained, in such manner as may be prescribed, all possible effects, complications and hazards`
  line `connected with the removal and transplantation to the donor and the recipient respectively.`
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (6524)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `Appropriate Authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00014_199442_1517807323753&sectionId=6524&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00014_199442_1517807323753
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government shall appoint, by notification, one`
  line `or more officers as Appropriate Authorities for each of the Union territories for the purposes of this`
  line Act.
  line
  line `(2) The State Government shall appoint, by notification, one or more officers as Appropriate`
  line `Authorities for the purposes of this Act.`
  line
  line `(3) The Appropriate Authority shall perform the following functions, namely:--`
  line
  line `(i) to grant registration under sub-section (1) of section 15 or renew registration under`
  line `sub-section (3) of that section;`
  line
  line `(ii) to suspend or cancel registration under sub-section (2) of section 16;`
  line
  line `^1[(iii) to enforce such standards, as may be prescribed,--`
  line
  line `(A) for hospitals engaged in the removal, storage or transplantation of any human organ:`
  line
  line `(B) for Tissue Banks engaged in recovery, screening, testing, processing, storage and`
  line `distribution of tissues;]`
  line
  line `(iv) to investigate any complaint of breach of any of the provisions of this Act or any of the`
  line `rules made thereunder and take appropriate action;`
  line
  line `^2[(iva) to inspect Tissue Banks periodically;]`
  line
  line `(v) to inspect hospitals periodically for examination of the quality of transplantation and the`
  line `follow-up medical care to persons who have undergone transplantation and persons from whom`
  line `organs are removed; and`
  line
  line `(vi) to undertake such other measures as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by s. 9, ibid., for clause (iii) (w.e.f. 10-1-2014).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by s. 9, ibid. (w.e.f. 10-1-2014).`
obj_root_law_sections_13_a:
  sectionId (6525)
  sectionNo 13A
  orderNo 14
  title `Advisory Committees to advise Appropriate Authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 10, ibid. (w.e.f. 10-1-2014).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00014_199442_1517807323753&sectionId=6525&sectionno=13A&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00014_199442_1517807323753
obj_root_law_sections_13_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[13A. Advisory Committees to advise Appropriate Authority.-- (1) The Central Government and`
  line `and the State Governments, as the case may be, by notification, shall constitute an Advisory Committee`
  line `for a period of two years to aid and advise the Appropriate Authority to discharge its functions.`
  line
  line `(2) The Advisory Committee shall consist of--`
  line
  line `(a) one administrative expert not below the rank of Secretary to the State Government, to be`
  line `nominated as Chairperson of the Advisory Committee;`
  line
  line `(b) two medical experts having such qualifications as may be prescribed;`
  line
  line `(c) one officer not below the rank of a Joint Director to represent the Ministry or Department`
  line `of Health and Family Welfare, to be designated as Member-Secretary;`
  line
  line `(d) two eminent social workers of high social standing and integrity, one of whom shall be`
  line `from amongst representatives of womens organisation;`
  line
  line `(e) one legal expert who has held the position of an Additional District Judge or equivalent;`
  line
  line `(f) one person to represent non-governmental organisations or associations which are working`
  line `in the field of organ or tissue donations or human rights;`
  line
  line `(g) one specialist in the field of human organ transplantation, provided he is not a member of`
  line `the transplantation team.`
  line
  line `(3) The terms and conditions for appointment to the Advisory Committee shall be such as may be`
  line `prescribed by the Central Government.]`
obj_root_law_sections_13_b:
  sectionId (6526)
  sectionNo 13B
  orderNo 15
  title `Powers of Appropriate Authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_b_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 10, ibid. (w.e.f. 10-1-2014).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00014_199442_1517807323753&sectionId=6526&sectionno=13B&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00014_199442_1517807323753
obj_root_law_sections_13_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[13B. Powers of Appropriate Authority.--The Appropriate Authority shall for the purposes of this`
  line `Act have all the powers of a civil court trying a suit under the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908)`
  line `and, in particular, in respect of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) summoning of any person who is in possession of any information relating to violation of the`
  line `provisions of this Act or the rules made thereunder;`
  line
  line `(b) discovery and production of any document or material object;`
  line
  line `(c) issuing search warrant for any place suspected to be indulging in unauthorised removal,`
  line `procurement or transplantation of human organs or tissues or both; and`
  line
  line `(d) any other matter which may be prescribed.]`
obj_root_law_sections_13_c:
  sectionId (6527)
  sectionNo 13C
  orderNo 16
  title `National Human Organs or tissues or both and Tissues Removal and Storage Network.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_c_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 10, ibid. (w.e.f. 10-1-2014).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00014_199442_1517807323753&sectionId=6527&sectionno=13C&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00014_199442_1517807323753
obj_root_law_sections_13_c_content:
  string
  line `^1[13C. National Human Organs and Tissues Removal and Storage Network.--The Central`
  line `Government may, by notification, establish a National Human Organs and Tissues Removal and Storage`
  line `Network at one or more places and Regional Network in such manner and to perform such functions, as`
  line `may be prescribed.]`
obj_root_law_sections_13_d:
  sectionId (6528)
  sectionNo 13D
  orderNo 17
  title `National registry.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_d_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 10, ibid. (w.e.f. 10-1-2014).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00014_199442_1517807323753&sectionId=6528&sectionno=13D&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00014_199442_1517807323753
obj_root_law_sections_13_d_content:
  string
  line `^1[13D. National registry.--The Central Government shall maintain a national registry of the donors`
  line `and recipients of human organs and tissues and such registry shall have such information as may be`
  line `prescribed to an ongoing evaluation of the scientific and clinical status of human organs and tissue.]`
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (6529)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 18
  title `Registration of hospitals engaged in removal, storage or transplantation of human organs or tissues or both.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00014_199442_1517807323753&sectionId=6529&sectionno=14&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00014_199442_1517807323753
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `14. Registration of hospitals engaged in removal, storage or transplantation of`
  line `^1[human organs or tissues or both].--(1) ^2[No hospital (including Human Organ Retrieval Centre)] shall`
  line `commence any activity relating to the removal, storage or transplantation of any ^3[human organ or`
  line `tissue or both] for therapeutic purposes after the commencement of this Act unless such hospital is duly`
  line `registered under this Act:`
  line
  line `Provided that every hospital engaged, either partly or exclusively, in any activity relating to`
  line `the removal, storage or transplantation of any ^3[human organ or tissue or both] for therapeutic`
  line `purposes immediately before the commencement of this Act, shall apply for registration within`
  line `sixty days from the date of such commencement:`
  line
  line `Provided further that every hospital engaged in any activity relating to the removal, storage or`
  line `transplantation of any ^3[human organ or tissue or both] shall cease to engage in any such activity on the`
  line `expiry of three months from the date of commencement of this Act unless such hospital has applied`
  line `for registration and is go registered or till such application is disposed of, whichever is earlier.`
  line
  line `(2) Every application for registration under sub-section (1) shall be made to the Appropriate`
  line `Authority in such form and in such manner and shall be accompanied by such fees as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) No hospital shall be registered under this Act unless the Appropriate Authority is satisfied that`
  line `such hospital is in a position to provide such specialised services and facilities, possess) such skilled`
  line `manpower and equipments and maintain such standards as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `^4[(4) No hospital shall be registered under this Act, unless the Appropriate Authority is satisfied that`
  line `such hospital has appointed a transplant coordinator having such qualifications and experience as may be`
  line prescribed.]
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act of 16 of 2011, s. 4, for "human organs" (w.e.f. 10-1-2014).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 11, ibid., for "No hospital" (w.e.f. 10-1-2014).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by s. 4, ibid., for "human organ" (w.e.f. 10-1-2014).`
  line
  line `4. Ins. by Act 16 of 2011, s. 11 (w.e.f. 10-1-2014).`
obj_root_law_sections_14_a:
  sectionId (6530)
  sectionNo 14A
  orderNo 19
  title `Registration of Tissue Bank.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_a_content
  footnotes `1. ns. by s. 12, ibid. (w.e.f. 10-1-2014).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00014_199442_1517807323753&sectionId=6530&sectionno=14A&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00014_199442_1517807323753
obj_root_law_sections_14_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[14A. Registration of Tissue Bank.-- (1) No Tissue Bank shall, after the commencement of the`
  line `Transplantation of Human Organs (Amendment) Act, 2011 (16 of 2011), commence any activity relating`
  line `to the recovery, screening, testing, processing, storage and distribution of tissues unless it is duly`
  line `registered under this Act:`
  line
  line `Provided that any facility engaged, either party or exlusively, in any activity relating to the recovery,`
  line `screening, testing, processing, storage and distribution of tissues immediately before the commencement`
  line `of the Transplantation of Human Organs (Amendment) Act, 2011 (16 of 2011), shall apply for`
  line `registration as Tissues Bank within sixty days from the date of such commencement:`
  line
  line `Provided further that such facility shall cease to engage in any such activity on the expiry of three`
  line `months from the date of commencement of the Transplantation of Human Organs (Amendement)`
  line `Act, 2011 (16 of 2011), unless such Tissue Bank has applied for registration and is so registered, or till`
  line `such application is disposed of, whichever is earlier.`
  line
  line `(2) Every application for registration under sub-section (1) shall be made to the Appropriate`
  line `Authority in such form and in such manner and shall be accompanied by such fees as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) No Tissue Bank shall be registered under this Act unless the Appropriate Authority is satisfied`
  line `that such Tissue Bank is in a position to provide such specialised service and facilities, possess such`
  line `skilled manpower and equipments and maintain such standards as may be prescribed.]`
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (6531)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 20
  title `Certificate of registration.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 13, ibid., for "grant to the hospital" (w.e.f. 10-1-2014).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00014_199442_1517807323753&sectionId=6531&sectionno=15&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00014_199442_1517807323753
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Appropriate Authority shall, after holding an inquiry and`
  line `after satisfying itself that the applicant has complied with all the requirements of this Act and the rules`
  line `made thereunder,`
  line
  line `^1[grant to the hospital or to the tissue Bank, as the case may be,] a certificate of`
  line `registration in such form, for such period and subject to such conditions as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) If, after the inquiry and after giving an opportunity to the applicant of being heard, the`
  line `Appropriate Authority is satisfied that the applicant has not complied with the requirement of this Act`
  line `and the rules made thereunder, it shall, for reasons to be recorded in writing, reject the application for`
  line registration.
  line
  line `(3) Every certificate of registration shall be renewed in such manner and on payment of such fees as`
  line `may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (6532)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 21
  title `Suspension or cancellation of registration.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00014_199442_1517807323753&sectionId=6532&sectionno=16&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00014_199442_1517807323753
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Appropriate Authority may,`
  line `suo motu or on complaint, issue a notice to any ^1[hospital or Tissue Bank, as the case may be,] to show`
  line `cause why its registration under this Act should not be suspended or cancelled for the reasons mentioned`
  line `in the notice.`
  line
  line `(2) If, after giving a reasonable opportunity of being heard to the ^1[hospital or Tissue Bank, as the`
  line `case may be,] the Appropriate Authority is satisfied that there has been a breach of any of the provisions`
  line `of this Act or the rules made thereunder, it may, without prejudice to any criminal action that it may`
  line `take against such ^1[hospital or Tissue Bank, as the case may be,] suspend its registration for such period`
  line `as it may think fit or cancel its registration:`
  line
  line `Provided that where the Appropriate Authority is of the opinion that it is necessary or expedient so to`
  line `do in the public interest, it may, for reasons to be recorded in writing, suspend the registration of any`
  line `^2[hospital or Tissue Bank, as the case may be,] without issuing any notice.`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by s. 14, ibid., for "hospital" (w.e.f. 10-1-2014).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 16 of 2011, s. 14, for "hospital" (w.e.f. 10-1-2014).`
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (6533)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 22
  title Appeals.
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 15, ibid. (w.e.f. 10-1-2014).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00014_199442_1517807323753&sectionId=6533&sectionno=17&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00014_199442_1517807323753
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `Any person aggrieved by an order of the Authorisation Committee rejecting an`
  line `application for approval under sub-section (6) of section 9, or any hospital ^1[or Tissue Bank, as the case`
  line `may be,] aggrieved by an order of the Appropriate Authority rejecting an application for registration`
  line `under sub-section (2) of section 15 or an order of suspension or cancellation of registration under`
  line `sub-section (2) of section 16, may, within thirty days from the date of the receipt of the order, prefer an`
  line `appeal, in such manner as may be prescribed, against such order to--`
  line
  line `(i) the Central Government where the appeal is against the order of the Authorisation Committee`
  line `constituted under clause (a) of sub-section (4) of section 9 or against the order of the Appropriate`
  line `Authority appointed under sub-section (1) of section 13; or`
  line
  line `(ii) the State Government, where the appeal is against the order of the Authorisation Committee`
  line `constituted under clause (b) of sub-section (4) of section 9 or against the order of the Appropriate`
  line `Authority appointed under sub-section (2) of section 13.`
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (6534)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 23
  title `Punishment for removal of human organ without authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00014_199442_1517807323753&sectionId=6534&sectionno=18&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00014_199442_1517807323753
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any person who renders his`
  line `services to or at any hospital and who, for purposes of transplantation, conducts, associates with, or helps`
  line `in any manner in, the removal of any human organ without authority, shall be punishable with`
  line `imprisonment for a term which may extend to ^1[ten years and with fine which may extend to twenty lakh`
  line rupees].
  line
  line `(2) Where any person convicted under sub-section (1) is a registered medical practitioner, his`
  line `name shall be reported by the Appropriate Authority to the respective State Medical Council for`
  line `taking necessary action including the removal of his name from the register of the Council for a`
  line `period of ^2[three years] for the first offence and permanently for the subsequent offence.`
  line
  line `^3[(3) Any person who renders his services to or at any hospital and who conducts, or associates with`
  line `or helps in any manner in the removal of human tissue without authority, shall be punishable with`
  line `imprisonment for a term which may extend to three years and with fine which may extend to five lakh`
  line rupees.]
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by s. 16, ibid., for "five years and with fine which may extend to ten thousand rupees" (w.e.f. 10-1-2014).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 16, ibid., for "two years" (w.e.f. 10-1-2014).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by s. 16, ibid. (w.e.f. 10-1-2014).`
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (6535)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 24
  title `Punishment for commercial dealings in human organs.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00014_199442_1517807323753&sectionId=6535&sectionno=19&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00014_199442_1517807323753
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line Whoever--
  line
  line `(a) makes or receives any payment for the supply of, or for an offer to supply, any human organ;`
  line
  line `(b) seeks to find a person willing to supply for payment any human organ;`
  line
  line `(c) offers to supply any human organ for payment; or`
  line
  line `(d) initiates or negotiates any arrangement involving the making of any payment for the supply`
  line `of, or for an offer to supply, any human organ;`
  line
  line `(e) takes part in the management or control of a body of persons, whether a society, firm or`
  line `company, whose activities consist of or include the initiation or negotiation of any arrangement`
  line `referred to in clause (d); or`
  line
  line `(f) publishes or distributes or causes to be published or distributed any advertisement,--`
  line
  line `(a) inviting persons to supply for payment of any human organ;`
  line
  line `(b) offering to supply any human organ for payment; or`
  line
  line `(c) indicating that the advertiser is willing to initiate or negotiate any arrangement referred`
  line `to in clause (d);`
  line
  line `^1[(g) abets in the preparation or submission of false documents including giving false affidavits to`
  line `establish that the donor is making the donation of the human organs, as a near relative or by reason of`
  line `affection or attachment towards the recipient,`
  line
  line `shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which shall not be less than ^2[five years but which`
  line `may extend to ten years and shall be liable to fine which shall not be less than twenty lakh rupees but`
  line `may extend to one crore rupees].`
  line
  line `^3* * * * *`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 16 of 2011, s. 17 (w.e.f. 10-1-2014).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 17, ibid., for "two years but which may extend to seven years and shall be liable to fine which shall not be less than`
  line `ten thousand rupees but may extend to twenty thousand rupees" (w.e.f. 10-1-2014).`
  line
  line `3. The proviso omitted by s. 17, ibid. (w.e.f. 10-1-2014).`
obj_root_law_sections_19_a:
  sectionId (6536)
  sectionNo 19A
  orderNo 25
  title `Punishment for illegal dealings in human tissues.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 18, ibid. (w.e.f. 10-1-2014).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00014_199442_1517807323753&sectionId=6536&sectionno=19A&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00014_199442_1517807323753
obj_root_law_sections_19_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[19A. Punishment for illegal dealings in human tissues.--Whoever--`
  line
  line `(a) makes or receives any payment for the supply of, or for an offer to supply, any human tissue;`
  line or
  line
  line `(b) seeks to find a person willing to supply for payment and human tissue; or`
  line
  line `(c) offers to supply any human tissue for payment; or`
  line
  line `(d) initiates or negotiates any arrangement involving the making of any payment for the supply`
  line `of, or for an offer to supply, any human tissue; or`
  line
  line `(e) takes part in the management or control of a body of persons, whether a society, firm or`
  line `company, whose activities consist of or include the initiation or negotiation of any arrangement`
  line `referred to in clause (d); or`
  line
  line `(f) publishes or distributes or causes to be published or distributed any advertisement--`
  line
  line `(i) inviting persons to supply for payment of any human tissue; or`
  line
  line `(ii) offering to supply any human tissue for payment; or`
  line
  line `(iii) indicating that the advertiser is willing to initiate or negotiate any arrangement referred to`
  line `in clause (d); or`
  line
  line `(g) abets in the preparation or submission of false documents including giving false affidavits to`
  line `establish that the donor is making the donation of the human tissues as a near relative or by reason of`
  line `affection or attachment towards the recipient,`
  line
  line `shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which shall not be less than one year but which may`
  line `extend to three years and shall be liable to fine which shall not be less than five lakh rupees but which`
  line `may extend to twenty-five lakh rupees.`
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (6537)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 26
  title `Punishment for contravention of any other provision of this Act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 19, ibid., for "three years or with fine which may extend to five thousand rupees" (w.e.f. 10-1-2014).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00014_199442_1517807323753&sectionId=6537&sectionno=20&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00014_199442_1517807323753
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `Whoever contravenes`
  line `any provision of this Act or any rule made, or any condition of the registration granted, thereunder for`
  line `which no punishment is separately provided in this Act, shall be punishable with imprisonment for a`
  line `term which may extend to ^1[five years or with fine which may extend to twenty lakh rupees].`
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (6538)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 27
  title `Offences by companies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00014_199442_1517807323753&sectionId=6538&sectionno=21&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00014_199442_1517807323753
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where any offence punishable under this Act has been`
  line `committed by a company, every person who, at the time the offence was committed was in charge of,`
  line `and was responsible to, the company for the conduct of the business of the company, as well as the`
  line `company, shall be deemed to be guilty of the offence and shall be liable to be proceeded against and`
  line `punished accordingly:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing contained in this sub-section shall render any such person liable to any`
  line `punishment, if he proves that the offence was committed without his knowledge or that be had`
  line `exercised all due diligence to prevent the commission of such offence.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), where any offence punishable under this`
  line `Act has been committed by a company and it is proved that the offence has been committed with the`
  line `consent or connivance of, or is attributable to any neglect on the part of, any director, manager, secretary or other officer of the company, such director, manager, secretary or other officer shall also be deemed to`
  line `be guilty of that offence and shall be liable to be proceeded against and punished accordingly.`
  line
  line `Explanation. -- For the purposes of this section,--`
  line
  line `(a) "company" means any body corporate and includes a firm or other association of`
  line `individuals; and`
  line
  line `(b) "director" in relation to a firm, means a partner in the firm.`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (6539)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 28
  title `Cognizance of offences.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00014_199442_1517807323753&sectionId=6539&sectionno=22&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00014_199442_1517807323753
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `(1) No court shall take cognizance of an offence under this Act except`
  line `on a complaint made by--`
  line
  line `(a) the Appropriate Authority concerned, or any officer authorised in this behalf by the`
  line `Central Government or the State Government or, as the case may be, the Appropriate Authority;`
  line or;
  line
  line `(b) a person who has given notice of not less than sixty days, in such manner as may be`
  line `prescribed, to the Appropriate Authority concerned, of the alleged offence and of his intention to`
  line `make a complaint to the court.`
  line
  line `(2) No court other than that of a Metropolitan Magistrate or a Judicial Magistrate of the first class`
  line `shall try any offence punishable under this Act.`
  line
  line `(3) Where a complaint has been made under clause (b) of sub-section (1), the court may, on`
  line `demand by such person, direct the Appropriate Authority to make available copies of the relevant`
  line `records in its possession to such person.`
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (6540)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 29
  title `Protection of action taken in good faith.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00014_199442_1517807323753&sectionId=6540&sectionno=23&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00014_199442_1517807323753
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `(1) No suit, prosecution or other legal`
  line `proceeding shall lie against any person for anything which is in good faith done or intended to be`
  line `done in pursuance of the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) No suit or other legal proceeding shall lie against the Central Government or the State`
  line `Government for any damage caused or likely to be caused for anything which is in good faith done`
  line `or intended to be done in pursuance of the provisions of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (6541)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 30
  title `Power to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00014_199442_1517807323753&sectionId=6541&sectionno=24&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00014_199442_1517807323753
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by notification, make rules for carrying`
  line `out the purposes of this Act.`
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the manner in which and the conditions subject to which any donor may authorise removal,`
  line `before his death, of any ^1[human organ or tissue or both] of his body under sub-section (1A) of`
  line `section 3;`
  line
  line `^2[(aa) the human organ or tissues or both in respect of which duty is cast on registered medical`
  line `pracitioner the manner of obtaining documentation of authoirsation under clause (i) of sub-section 3;`
  line
  line `(ab) the manner of informing the Human Organ Retrieval Centre under clause (iii) of`
  line `sub-section (1A) of section 3;`
  line
  line `(ac) the date from which duties mentioned in sub-section (1A) are applicable to registered`
  line `medical practitioner working a unregistered hospital under sub-section (1B) of section 3;`
  line
  line `(ae) the qualification and experience of a technician under the proviso to sub-section (4) of`
  line `section 3;]`
  line
  line `(b) the form and the manner in which a brain-stem death is to be certified and the conditions and`
  line `requirements which are to be satisfied for that purpose under sub-section (6) of section 3;`
  line
  line `^3[(ba) the conditions for nomination of a surgeon or a physician and an anaesthetist or intensivist`
  line `to be included in the Board of medical experts under the proviso to clause (iii) of sub-section (6) of`
  line `section 3;]`
  line
  line `(c) the form and the manner in which any of the parents may give authority, in the case of`
  line `brain-stem death of a minor, for the removal of any ^4[human organ or tissue or both] under`
  line `sub-section (7) of section 3;`
  line
  line `(d) the form in which authority for the removal of any ^4[human organ or tissue or both] from`
  line `an, unclaimed dead body may be given by the person incharge of the management or control of the`
  line `hospital or prison under sub-section (1) of section 5;`
  line
  line `(e) the steps to be taken for the preservation of the ^4[human organ or tissue or both] removed`
  line `from the body of any person, under section 7;`
  line
  line `^3[(ea) the manner of removal of human organs or tissues or both from the body of a minor before`
  line `his death for transplantation under sub-section (1B) of section 9;`
  line
  line `(eb) the composition of the Authorisation Committees under sub-section (4) of section 9;]`
  line
  line `(f) the form and the manner in which an application may be jointly made by the donor and the`
  line `recipient under sub-section (5) of section 9;`
  line
  line `(g) the manner in which all possible effects, complications and hazards connected with the`
  line `removal and transplantation is to be explained by the registered medical practitioner to the donor and`
  line `the recipient under section 12;`
  line
  line `(h) the standards as are to be enforced by the Appropriate Authority for hospitals engaged in`
  line `the removal, storage or transplantation of any ^4[human organ or tissue or both] under clause (iii) of`
  line `sub-section (3) of section 13;`
  line
  line `(i) the other measures as the Appropriate Authority shall undertake in performing its functions`
  line `under clause (vi) of sub-section (3) of section 13;`
  line
  line `^3[(ia) the qualifications of medical experts and the terms and conditions for appointment to`
  line `Advisory committee under sub-sections (2) and (3) of section 13A;`
  line
  line `(ib) the power of the Appropriate Authority in any other matter under clause (d) of section 13B;`
  line
  line `(ic) the manner of establishment of a National Human Organs and Tissues Removal and Storage`
  line `Network and Regional Network and functions to be performed by them under section 13C;`
  line
  line `(id) the information in the national registry of the donors and recipients of human organs and`
  line `tissues and all information under section 13D;]`
  line
  line `(j) the form and the manner in which an application for registration shall be made and the`
  line `fee which shall be accompanied, under sub-section (2) of section 14;`
  line
  line `(k) the specialised services and the facilities to be provided, skilled manpower and the`
  line `equipments to be possessed and the standards to be maintained by a hospital for registration,`
  line `under sub-section (3) of section 14;`
  line
  line `^3[(ka) the qualifications and experience of a transplant co-ordinator under sub-section (4) of`
  line `section 14;`
  line
  line `(kb) the form and the manner in which an application for registration shall be made and the fee`
  line `which shall be accompanied, under sub-section (2) of section 14A;`
  line
  line `(kc) the specialised service and the facilities to be provided, skilled manpower and the equipment`
  line `to be possessed and the standards to be maintained by a Tissue Bank, under sub-section (3) of`
  line `section 14A;]`
  line
  line `(l) the form in which, the period for which and the conditions subject to which certificate of`
  line `registration is to be granted to a ^5[hospital or Tissue Bank], under sub-section (1) of section 15;`
  line
  line `(m) the manner in which and the fee on payment of which certificate of registration is to be`
  line `renewed under sub-section (3) of section 15;`
  line
  line `(n) the manner in which an appeal may be preferred under section 17;`
  line
  line `(o) the manner in which a person is required to give notice to the Appropriate Authority of the`
  line `alleged offence and of his intention to make a complaint to the court, under clause (b) of`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 22; and`
  line
  line `(p) any other matter which is required to be, or may be, prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) Every rule made under this Act shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made, before each`
  line `House of Parliament, while it is in session, for a total period of thirty days which may be comprised in`
  line `one session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session immediately`
  line `following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in making any`
  line `modification in the rule or both Houses agree that the rule should not be made, the rule shall thereafter`
  line `have effect only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that any`
  line `such modification or annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done`
  line `under that rule.`
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act of 16 of 2011, s. 4 for "human organ" (w.e.f. 10-1-2014).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by s. 20, ibid. (w.e.f. 10-1-2014).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by Act 16 of 2011, s. 20 (w.e.f. 10-1-2014).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by s. 4, ibid., for "human organ" (w.e.f. 10-1-2014).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by Act 16 of 2011, s. 20, for "hospital" (w.e.f. 10-1-2014).`
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (6542)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 31
  title `Repeal and savings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00014_199442_1517807323753&sectionId=6542&sectionno=25&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00014_199442_1517807323753
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Ear Drums and Ear Bones (Authority for Use for Therapeutic`
  line `Purposes) Act, 1982 (28 of 1982) and the Eyes (Authority for Use for Therapeutic Purposes) Act, 1982`
  line `(29 of 1982) are hereby repealed.`
  line
  line `(2) The repeal shall, however, not affect the previous operation of the Acts so repealed or anything`
  line `duly done or suffered thereunder.`
obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes:
  string
  line
